[start]
[intro]
[verse]
Late night in the city lights are shining low
Saxophone is playing sweet and slow
The blues are calling from the depths of my soul
In this jazz bar I finally feel whole
[verse]
The piano keys are dancing under fingertips
Smooth jazz flowing like a river's gentle lips
